article.linkText: Fuller's 24 points lead UTSA past Houston Christian 89-87
article.story: HOUSTON -- — Dre Fuller Jr. scored 24 points as UTSA beat Houston Christian 89-87 on Monday night. Fuller was 8 of 15 shooting, including 3 for 7 from 3-point range, and went 5 for 5 from the line for the Roadrunners (2-3). Christian Tucker scored 15 points and added five rebounds and eight assists. Carlton Linguard finished 5 of 9 from the field to finish with 10 points, while adding six rebounds. The Huskies (0-3) were led in scoring by Marcus Greene, who finished with 23 points. Jay Alvarez added 19 points for Houston Christian. In addition, Michael Imariagbe had 17 points and 11 rebounds. ------ The Associated Press created this story using technology provided by Data Skrive and data from Sportradar.
